David Plass wrote:
&gt; Negative tests are different... I&#39;d write
&gt;     public void testExceptions() {    // note no throws         try {
&gt;             method.throwsNPE();
&gt;             fail(&quot;Should have thrown NPE&quot;);
&gt;         } catch (NullPointerException expected) {
&gt;             assertTrue(&quot;Should catch NPE&quot;, true);
&gt;         }
&gt;     }
&gt; 
&gt; to test the fact that &#39;method.throwsNPE&#39; should throw NPE.

Yep, though the assertTrue is kind of redundant, and I prefer the
assertThrows pattern.

And if the method is allowed to throw a new kind of exception, I might
write a such test to document the fact, but I wouldn&#39;t want to need to
adapt all the other tests, too...

Cheers, Ilja
